pkg/config/config.go.message:
I don't think it's a good idea, at least now. Currently config is loaded when you call any subcommand, starting from bootstrap, ending subcommands such as version. It's not good approach to see config missing error instead of version of application. So right now we have to fix this error by this approach. Once config load refactored - we can move it from here. Right now we have to get rid of panic firstly. 

And also if move it to config init - it would be the same code and more overload.
After config load refactor then code will look like this and will move to EnsureComplete I believe:

for clusterName, _ := range c.kubeConfig.Clusters {
		clusterComplexName := NewClusterComplexNameFromKubeClusterName(clusterName)
		if c.Clusters[clusterComplexName.Name].ClusterTypes == nil {
			return ErrMissingConfig{
				What: "clusterType is not defined for " + clusterComplexName.Name,
			}
		}
	}

